### Error Styling with Captions
**CRITICAL**: When using captions with form components that can have errors, the caption MUST be included within the component's legend/label HTML to ensure the error styling red line wraps around both the caption and heading.

**WRONG** (caption outside component - error line won't wrap around caption):
```nunjucks
<span class="govuk-caption-l">{{ data['project-name'] }}</span>
{{ govukRadios({
    fieldset: {
        legend: {
            text: pageHeadingTextHTML,
            isPageHeading: true,
            classes: "govuk-fieldset__legend--l"
        }
    },
    errorMessage: { text: "Error message" } if data['errorthispage'] == "true"
}) }}
```

**CORRECT** (caption inside component legend HTML - error line wraps around both):
```nunjucks
{{ govukRadios({
    fieldset: {
        legend: {
            html: '<span class="govuk-caption-l">' + data['project-name'] + '</span>' + pageHeadingTextHTML,
            isPageHeading: true,
            classes: "govuk-fieldset__legend--l"
        }
    },
    errorMessage: { text: "Error message" } if data['errorthispage'] == "true"
}) }}
```

This applies to ALL form components with legends/labels (govukRadios, govukCheckboxes, govukInput, etc.) when used with captions and error states.

